    <h2>What a Smart 30-30-30 Morning Looks Like After 40</h2>

    <p>Strip away the social media framing and what you're left with is a genuinely solid morning structure for men over 40:</p>

    <p><strong>Within an hour of waking:</strong> a meal that hits <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/30-gram-protein-rule/" style="color: var(--green); font-weight: 600;">30 grams of protein</a>. Three eggs and Greek yogurt. A protein shake and cottage cheese. A chicken-and-egg scramble. Whatever fits your routine — real food, no special products required.</p>

    <p><strong>Then 20–30 minutes of movement.</strong> A brisk walk is enough. If you can add some intensity — a faster pace, a short jog interval — the BDNF benefit increases. But consistent low-intensity movement every morning beats occasional harder sessions you skip half the time. Sustainability is the whole game.</p>

    <p><strong>Log the protein while you're eating it.</strong> Not after. Not later. The 30 seconds it takes to log your breakfast meal keeps the number visible for the rest of the day — which is what determines whether you hit your target or drift 40g short without noticing. That's the actual problem most men over 40 are dealing with. Not lack of effort. Lack of visibility.</p>

